  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pools &amp; Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>The hotel has two saltwater pools, as well as a children's pool, for you to choose from during your stay. They're all surrounded by plenty of sun beds and if you want to get out of the heat of the sun you'll find lots of lovely shady areas beneath the palm trees.</p>
<p>The pool close to the hotel's main building is surrounded by greenery and the bar beside it is open all day. We found it hard to tare ourselves away - especially when the staff serve delicious fruit smoothies and tasty cocktails to the poolside. The other pool is an infinity pool - it's a pretty special spot that looks out across the crystal clear sea. </p>
<p>The children's pool is shallower, so the kids can splash about safely. There's a nice grassy area beside the pool too, so it's perfect for playing and making new friends. </p>
<p><strong>Chia Bay</strong></p>
<p>There's lots of great beaches just a short drive from the hotel. Chia Bay is about 15 kilometres away - it's been awarded the most beautiful beach in Italy! We can see why - its surrounded by sand dunes and has beautiful white sand that's lapped by the clear blue sea. There's places where you can hire canoes and snorkelling equipment, or even have a surf lesson. It's a really nice area for walking too, with lots of beautiful unspoiled coves to stumble upon - some of them are only reachable on foot. The hotel runs a shuttle service here for a small local fee.</p>
<p><strong>Tuerredda Beach</strong></p>
<p>About 20 minutes drive from the hotel you'll find the beautiful little sheltered cove of Turredda. Spend a day here relaxing on the soft fine sand. It's hard not to be mesmerised by the ever changing shades of the water all mottled in turquoises and blues. </p>
<p><strong>Cala Zafferano Beach</strong></p>
<p>The only way to reach this beautiful remote beach is by boat. You can hire your own or take a boat trip (bookable and payable locally). The sand's made up of lots of glistening shell fragments and the water is so clear. </p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Massage treatments (payable locally)</li>
<li>Yoga lessons (payable locally)</li>
<li>18 hole golf course three kilometres away (payable locally)</li>
<li>Tennis court </li>
<li>Horse riding (payable locally)</li>
<li>Boat rental (payable locally)</li>
<li>Road bike and mountain bike rental (payable locally)</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Shuttle</strong></span></p>
<p>The hotel have a shuttle service that runs to Chia, Pula and Nora towns or beaches once per day. The service must be booked at reception the day before and is payable locally.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>General Facilities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Parking</li>
<li>24 hour reception</li>
<li>Babysitting available on request (payable locally)</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
